<br>
With 6 second pets I could avoid getting summoned before finishing my pet cast, but not avoid getting summoned immediately after.  I still need to try it again with 5 second pets.  This was using a reclaim chaining approach, spamming back off just as root landed, and reclaiming pet just after it got summoned.<br>
<br>
One thing I can suggest is if you are regular chaining, pretype /pet get lost, then start recasting your pet just as root lands.  Just after root lands, spam your Back button in the pet control window until the pet gets summoned.  The second you see the pet get summoned, hit enter.  You will have only a few seconds left for the new pet to pop, if that.  It will not be long enough for the mob's summon timer to be refreshed.  Then send the new pet in.<br>
<br>
That method should work reliably. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 653<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 6:41:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8527.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: All it takes</span><hr size=1> I use pet hold usually~ but maybe someone with servant of ro would wanna see if servant of ro is capable of being summoned by a mob. My idea for servant was that it's an escape tool since fully resisted spells give decent aggro~ but maybe it's just a useless skill. Think outside the box. <p>Happy trails.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=edano>Edano</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Limey Magician</span><br>  Posts: 915<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 7:58:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8527.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chaining summoning mobs</span><hr size=1> Mob summon refresh times vary by zone. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=86775&amp;resize=true" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.danos.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/deadgnome.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stehle>st