<br>
1.  debuff / pull<br>
2.  send pet in<br>
3.  when pet is about dead (how depends on how fast the damage is being dished out) i make sure I have the monster targeted and start casting a second pet<br>
4.  when second pet is about to pop (usually about 4 pct left in cast time) i hit the pet get lost button (or you can type it out, whichever you prefer).<br>
5.  as soon as second pet pops, spam the 'pet attack' button and it will attack the monster and hopefully quickly overwrite what little aggro you had from the debuff.<br>
6.  rinse and repeat.  when mob is at low enough health, nuke away.<br>
<br>
The only downside to this is that you can't reclaim the pet.  Unless, however, you had an insanely fast cast time and was using an earth pet that roots (and it held while you were summoning your second pet).<br>
<br>
All in all, insanely effecient manner to take down large mobs.  If you have BO3 or Lava Shield right clickies it is even better.<br>
<br>
Casala, lvl 54 Elementalist of Saryn (not for long-- finally)<br>
<br>
